</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33F6542E07D0A34FF0DF805FE5EFF4E" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="5" pageNumber="562" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9A36C9E07D0A34FF0DF805FE5EFF4E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1186,2041]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,251]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="B951EADBE07D0A37FF0DF805FE82F805" bold="true" box="[199,308,1942,1968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species occurs in two forms, one with hind wings well developed (macropterous) and another with hind wings absent (brachypterous). These forms differ morphologically as indicated in the genus description as far as the structure of the forewings and the thorax are concerned. 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D4AE07D0A37FC52F84CFB84F84D" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2019" box="[920,1074,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sudindicus">
<emphasis id="B951EADBE07D0A37FC52F84CFB84F84D" box="[920,1074,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">D. sudindicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D4AE07E0A34FF5DFF09FEAEFF06" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,280,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B951EADBE07E0A34FF5DFF09FEAEFF06" box="[151,280,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">D. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in being more slender and longer in addition to the characters of the male genitalia. This species is unique among the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D4AE07E0A34FD49FF2EFCB5FF62" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1916" box="[643,771,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EADBE07E0A34FD49FF2EFCB5FF62" box="[643,771,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Daimachus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having triangular projections on both dorsal and ventral surfaces of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
